race.comment: LUCK IS A LADY (6) raced once in the maiden preparation when sixth at Oaklawn Park (Dirt) over 1207m back on March 1. Can improve sharply and is expected to feature. LUCY'S HALO (5) is ready to break through after collecting her 4th minor placing in a row last time over 1207m at this track (Dirt) after being in the firing line all the way. Nicely placed to feature in the finish. MISS CODE (10) is a well-related three-year-old filly making her first appearance at the races. By Code West from Inca Miss who has produced some fine gallopers, including winners at black type level. Sure to be competitive despite a difficult gate. GOSPEL CESS (11) was in the firing line on the bend and finished third last start over 1207m at this track (Dirt), beaten 12 lengths. Should take a lot from that hit-out. Nicely placed to fill a top-three spot again.
